                <head>No. 350.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bead</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 3, 1874</date>. (Received April
                        30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 15.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have been
                    requested by many highly respectable and influential citizens to pray the
                    Government not to increase the duty upon dried currants. * * * A number of Greek
                    and American merchants have lately learned that a proposition is before the
                    House of Representatives to double this importation tax.</p>
                <p>Commending the subject anew to the favorable notice of the Department, and
                    referring to previous elaborate communications upon this subject,</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN MEREDITH READ, <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
